scm.corner.R is vendored verbatim from the SCM-Debug repository:

    https://github.com/Xun90/SCM-Debug  (file scm.corner.R)
    Copyright (c) 2021 Xun Zhou -- MIT License (full text below).

It implements the bilevel synthetic-control solver of

    Malo, P., Eskelinen, J., Zhou, X., & Kuosmanen, T. (2024). Computing
    Synthetic Controls Using Bilevel Optimization. (MPRA Paper 104085);
    Kuosmanen, T., Zhou, X., Eskelinen, J., & Malo, P. (2021). Design Flaw of
    the Synthetic Control Method. (MPRA Paper 106390).

It is bundled here (rather than fetched at run time) so the malo_basque
cross-validation reference is reproducible offline; the repository is reachable
only via the codeload tarball in this sandbox (git clone is proxy-blocked), and
benchmarks/reference/.cache/ is gitignored. install_scmcorner.sh documents the
upstream fetch. The function consumes only quadprog/limSolve/lpSolve/kernlab QP
and LP solvers; no modifications were made.

